client_certificate.description: Public certificate used by clients to authenticate to the cluster endpoint.

client_key.description: Private key used by clients to authenticate to the cluster endpoint.

cluster_ca_certificate.description: The public certificate that is the root of trust for the cluster.

cluster_endpoint.description: The IP address of the cluster master.

client_certificate.description: Public certificate used by clients to authenticate to the cluster endpoint.

client_key.description: Private key used by clients to authenticate to the cluster endpoint.

cluster_ca_certificate.description: The public certificate that is the root of trust for the cluster.

endpoint.description: The IP address of the cluster master.

name.description: The name of the cluster master. This output is used for interpolation with node pools, other modules.

alternative_default_service_account.description: Alternative Service Account to be used by the Node VMs. If not specified, the default compute Service Account will be used. Provide if the default Service Account is no longer available.

basic_auth_password.description: The password used for basic auth; set both this and `basic_auth_username` to "" to disable basic auth.

basic_auth_username.description: The username used for basic auth; set both this and `basic_auth_password` to "" to disable basic auth.

cluster_secondary_range_name.description: The name of the secondary range within the subnetwork for the cluster to use

disable_public_endpoint.description: Control whether the master's internal IP address is used as the cluster endpoint. If set to 'true', the master can only be accessed from internal IP addresses.

enable_client_certificate_authentication.description: Whether to enable authentication by x509 certificates. With ABAC disabled, these certificates are effectively useless.

enable_legacy_abac.description: Whether to enable legacy Attribute-Based Access Control (ABAC). RBAC has significant security advantages over ABAC.

enable_network_policy.description: Whether to enable Kubernetes NetworkPolicy on the master, which is required to be enabled to be used on Nodes.

enable_private_nodes.description: Control whether nodes have internal IP addresses only. If enabled, all nodes are given only RFC 1918 private addresses and communicate with the master via private networking.

enable_vertical_pod_autoscaling.description: Whether to enable Vertical Pod Autoscaling

enable_workload_identity.description: Enable Workload Identity on the cluster

gsuite_domain_name.description: The domain name for use with Google security groups in Kubernetes RBAC. If a value is provided, the cluster will be initialized with security group `gke-security-groups@[yourdomain.com]`.

horizontal_pod_autoscaling.description: Whether to enable the horizontal pod autoscaling addon

http_load_balancing.description: Whether to enable the http (L7) load balancing addon

identity_namespace.description: Workload Identity Namespace. Default sets project based namespace [project_id].svc.id.goog

ip_masq_link_local.description: Whether to masquerade traffic to the link-local prefix (169.254.0.0/16).

ip_masq_resync_interval.description: The interval at which the agent attempts to sync its ConfigMap file from the disk.

kubernetes_version.description: The Kubernetes version of the masters. If set to 'latest' it will pull latest available version in the selected region.

location.description: The location (region or zone) to host the cluster in

logging_service.description: The logging service that the cluster should write logs to. Available options include logging.googleapis.com/kubernetes, logging.googleapis.com (legacy), and none

maintenance_start_time.description: Time window specified for daily maintenance operations in RFC3339 format

master_ipv4_cidr_block.description: The IP range in CIDR notation to use for the hosted master network. This range will be used for assigning internal IP addresses to the master or set of masters, as well as the ILB VIP. This range must not overlap with any other ranges in use within the cluster's network.

monitoring_service.description: The monitoring service that the cluster should write metrics to. Automatically send metrics from pods in the cluster to the Stackdriver Monitoring API. VM metrics will be collected by Google Compute Engine regardless of this setting. Available options include monitoring.googleapis.com/kubernetes, monitoring.googleapis.com (legacy), and none

network.description: A reference (self link) to the VPC network to host the cluster in

network_project.description: The project ID of the shared VPC's host (for shared vpc support)

non_masquerade_cidrs.description: List of strings in CIDR notation that specify the IP address ranges that do not use IP masquerading.

project.description: The project ID to host the cluster in

resource_labels.description: The GCE resource labels (a map of key/value pairs) to be applied to the cluster.

secrets_encryption_kms_key.description: The Cloud KMS key to use for the encryption of secrets in etcd, e.g: projects/my-project/locations/global/keyRings/my-ring/cryptoKeys/my-key

services_secondary_range_name.description: The name of the secondary range within the subnetwork for the services to use

stub_domains.description: Map of stub domains and their resolvers to forward DNS queries for a certain domain to an external DNS server

subnetwork.description: A reference (self link) to the subnetwork to host the cluster in

email.description: The email address of the custom service account.

description.description: The description of the custom service account.

name.description: The name of the custom service account. This parameter is limited to a maximum of 28 characters.

project.description: The name of the GCP Project where all resources will be launched.

service_account_roles.description: Additional roles to be added to the service account.

network.description: A reference (self_link) to the VPC network

private.description: The network tag string used for the private access tier

private_persistence.description: The network tag string used for the private-persistence access tier

private_subnetwork.description: A reference (self_link) to the private subnetwork

public.description: The network tag string used for the public access tier

public_restricted.description: The string of the public tag

public_subnetwork.description: A reference (self_link) to the public subnetwork

private_persistence.description: The string of the private-persistence tag

public.description: The string of the public tag

public_restricted.description: The string of the public tag

allowed_public_restricted_subnetworks.description: The public networks that is allowed access to the public_restricted subnetwork of the network

name_prefix.description: A name prefix used in resource names to ensure uniqueness across a project.

network.description: A reference (self_link) to the VPC network to apply firewall rules to

private_subnetwork.description: A reference (self_link) to the private subnetwork of the network

project.description: The project to create the firewall rules in. Must match the network project.

public_subnetwork.description: A reference (self_link) to the public subnetwork of the network

allowed_public_restricted_subnetworks.description: The public networks that is allowed access to the public_restricted subnetwork of the network

cidr_block.description: The IP address range of the VPC in CIDR notation. A prefix of /16 is recommended. Do not use a prefix higher than /27.

cidr_subnetwork_spacing.description: How many subnetwork-mask sized spaces to leave between each subnetwork type.

cidr_subnetwork_width_delta.description: The difference between your network and subnetwork netmask; an /16 network and a /20 subnetwork would be 4.

log_config.description: The logging options for the subnetwork flow logs. Setting this value to `null` will disable them. See https://www.terraform.io/docs/providers/google/r/compute_subnetwork.html for more information and examples.

name_prefix.description: A name prefix used in resource names to ensure uniqueness across a project.

private_services_secondary_cidr_block.description: The IP address range of the VPC's private services secondary address range in CIDR notation. A prefix of /16 is recommended. Do not use a prefix higher than /27. Note: this variable is optional and is used primarily for backwards compatibility, if not specified a range will be calculated using var.secondary_cidr_block, var.secondary_cidr_subnetwork_width_delta and var.secondary_cidr_subnetwork_spacing.

project.description: The project ID for the network

public_services_secondary_cidr_block.description: The IP address range of the VPC's public services secondary address range in CIDR notation. A prefix of /16 is recommended. Do not use a prefix higher than /27. Note: this variable is optional and is used primarily for backwards compatibility, if not specified a range will be calculated using var.secondary_cidr_block, var.secondary_cidr_subnetwork_width_delta and var.secondary_cidr_subnetwork_spacing.

public_services_secondary_range_name.description: The name associated with the services subnetwork secondary range, used when adding an alias IP range to a VM instance. The name must be 1-63 characters long, and comply with RFC1035. The name must be unique within the subnetwork.

public_subnetwork_secondary_range_name.description: The name associated with the pod subnetwork secondary range, used when adding an alias IP range to a VM instance. The name must be 1-63 characters long, and comply with RFC1035. The name must be unique within the subnetwork.

region.description: The region for subnetworks in the network

secondary_cidr_block.description: The IP address range of the VPC's secondary address range in CIDR notation. A prefix of /16 is recommended. Do not use a prefix higher than /27.

secondary_cidr_subnetwork_spacing.description: How many subnetwork-mask sized spaces to leave between each subnetwork type's secondary ranges.

secondary_cidr_subnetwork_width_delta.description: The difference between your network and subnetwork's secondary range netmask; an /16 network and a /20 subnetwork would be 4.

cluster_name.description: The name of the Kubernetes cluster.

cluster_service_account_description.default: Example GKE Cluster Service Account managed by Terraform
cluster_service_account_description.description: A description of the custom service account used for the GKE cluster.

cluster_service_account_name.description: The name of the custom service account used for the GKE cluster. This parameter is limited to a maximum of 28 characters.

kubectl_config_path.description: Path to the kubectl config file. Defaults to $HOME/.kube/config

master_ipv4_cidr_block.description: The IP range in CIDR notation (size must be /28) to use for the hosted master network. This range will be used for assigning internal IP addresses to the master or set of masters, as well as the ILB VIP. This range must not overlap with any other ranges in use within the cluster's network.

private_services_secondary_cidr_block.description: The IP address range of the VPC's private services secondary address range in CIDR notation. A prefix of /16 is recommended. Do not use a prefix higher than /27. Note: this variable is optional and is used primarily for backwards compatibility, if not specified a range will be calculated using var.secondary_cidr_block, var.secondary_cidr_subnetwork_width_delta and var.secondary_cidr_subnetwork_spacing.

public_services_secondary_cidr_block.description: The IP address range of the VPC's public services secondary address range in CIDR notation. A prefix of /16 is recommended. Do not use a prefix higher than /27. Note: this variable is optional and is used primarily for backwards compatibility, if not specified a range will be calculated using var.secondary_cidr_block, var.secondary_cidr_subnetwork_width_delta and var.secondary_cidr_subnetwork_spacing.

public_services_secondary_range_name.description: The name associated with the services subnetwork secondary range, used when adding an alias IP range to a VM instance. The name must be 1-63 characters long, and comply with RFC1035. The name must be unique within the subnetwork.

public_subnetwork_secondary_range_name.description: The name associated with the pod subnetwork secondary range, used when adding an alias IP range to a VM instance. The name must be 1-63 characters long, and comply with RFC1035. The name must be unique within the subnetwork.

secondary_cidr_subnetwork_spacing.description: How many subnetwork-mask sized spaces to leave between each subnetwork type's secondary ranges.

secondary_cidr_subnetwork_width_delta.description: The difference between your network and subnetwork's secondary range netmask; an /16 network and a /20 subnetwork would be 4.

vpc_cidr_block.description: The IP address range of the VPC in CIDR notation. A prefix of /16 is recommended. Do not use a prefix higher than /27.

vpc_secondary_cidr_block.description: The IP address range of the VPC's secondary address range in CIDR notation. A prefix of /16 is recommended. Do not use a prefix higher than /27.
